Grok's Page Analysis
Analysis: Saved Analyses Tab (Empty State)

1. Bugs/UX Issues

Extremely barren empty state — just text and a generic button creates high cognitive load.
"Grok" branding in button may confuse users who don't know the AI is called Grok.
No visual hierarchy or illustration, making the meta-tab feel broken rather than intentional.
Button text "Analyse Page with Grok" is contextually wrong on a meta-tab.
2. Actionable Improvements

Replace with rich empty state: illustration + 2-sentence value prop + primary "Analyse Current Page with Grok" button.
Add secondary "View Sample Analysis" button that loads a pre-made demo.
Include a short "How it works" collapsible with 3-step explanation.
Add subtle "Auto-save toggle" hint so users understand the value before they create their first analysis.
3. Ideas for $500 Users (Premium Tier)

"Smart Folders" + AI auto-tagging of feedback by theme/severity/product area.
Trend analysis dashboard across all saved analyses (sentiment over time, recurring issues).
One-click "Generate Executive Summary" across multiple saved analyses.
Export as branded PDF/Deck with their logo and custom Grok prompt templates.
Priority Grok model access (faster + higher quality) for analysis generation.
4. Code Optimisations

Convert static empty state to a reusable EmptyState component with props for different contexts.
Add Suspense + skeleton state so future populated view doesn't cause layout shift.
Cache last used Grok analysis prompt in localStorage for this tab.
Use React.memo + proper key strategy in preparation for the analysis list render.
Priority Recommendation: Fix the empty state UX immediately — it's currently the weakest onboarding moment in the entire tool.